author: Good Enough
description:
Nanga Parbat, known as the “Killer Mountain” is one of the deadliest peaks on Earth. Rising 8,126 meters (26,660 ft) in Pakistan’s Himalayas, it has claimed the lives of countless climbers who dared to challenge its sheer walls and unpredictable weather. With a fatality rate among the highest of any 8,000-meter peak, Nanga Parbat is one of the most terrifying mountain on the planet.
